An oil spill stretching at least two miles long occurs in the Arabian Sea offshore Mumbai, India, after a vessel from Panama collides with another vessel from St. Kitts. The Panamanian ship was carrying 2,662 tons of oil, 283 tons of diesel and 88,040 liters of lube oil when it became grounded and started to leak. (CNN) (Sify)An oil spill becomes more serious three days after two ships, MSC Chitra and MV Khalijia-111 collided off Mumbai, India. (The Times of India) (Aljazeera)The death toll in China following the recent mudslide rises to 337. 1,148 people are now missing. (BBC) (AFP via France24) (AP via The Times of India) (Reuters India)